VALUES
(40, 21, 22, 62, 5, 14, 15, 'whatsoever ye shall ask in prayer', 'Connection of Prayer and Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of asking in prayer with belief and confidence. Matthew highlights receiving what is asked for in prayer, while 1 John assures that requests made according to God''s will are heard and granted.', 'theme', 0.6499999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 22, 62, 3, 22, 22, 'whatsoever ye shall ask in prayer', 'Connection of Prayer and Commandments', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of asking in prayer and receiving from God. Matthew highlights belief in prayer, while 1 John connects receiving to keeping commandments and pleasing God.', 'theme', 0.573, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 22, 40, 18, 19, 19, 'ask in prayer, believing', 'Connection of Prayer and Agreement', 'Both passages emphasize the power of prayer and belief in receiving what is asked. Matthew 21:22 highlights asking in prayer with belief, while Matthew 18:19 focuses on the agreement in prayer among two individuals.', 'theme', 0.5589999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 22, 43, 14, 13, 13, 'whatsoever ye shall ask', 'Connection of Prayer and Asking', 'Both passages emphasize the act of asking in prayer. Matthew highlights belief in receiving, while John focuses on asking in Jesus'' name.', 'theme', 0.5589999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 22, 59, 5, 16, 16, 'ask in prayer, believing', 'Connection of Prayer and Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the power of prayer. Matthew highlights receiving through belief, while James underscores the effectiveness of fervent prayer by the righteous.', 'theme', 0.552, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 23, 44, 4, 7, 7, 'By what authority doest thou these things?', 'Authority and Power in Ministry', 'This connection highlights the questioning of authority in both passages. In Matthew, the chief priests inquire about Jesus'' authority, while in Acts, the leaders question the apostles about the power behind their actions.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 23, 41, 11, 27, 33, 'By what authority doest thou these things?', 'Authority Questioned by Leaders', 'Both passages emphasize the challenge to Jesus'' authority by the chief priests and elders. They ask, ''By what authority doest thou these things?'' highlighting a direct confrontation in both accounts.', 'parallel', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 23, 13, 24, 1, 19, 'By what authority doest thou these things?', 'Authority in Priesthood', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of authority within the priesthood. In Matthew, the question of authority is raised regarding Jesus'' actions, while 1 Chronicles details the established order and divisions of the priests, highlighting their roles and authority in service to God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 23, 2, 2, 14, 14, 'By what authority doest thou these things?', 'Authority and Leadership Questions', 'Both passages emphasize questioning authority and leadership. In Matthew, the chief priests challenge Jesus'' authority, while in Exodus, the Israelites question Moses'' role as a leader.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 23, 40, 26, 55, 55, NULL, 'Authority and Teaching in the Temple', 'This connection highlights Jesus'' authority in teaching and the response of the religious leaders. Both passages emphasize his presence in the temple and the challenge to his authority, culminating in the arrest narrative.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 23, 44, 7, 27, 27, 'By what authority doest thou these things?', 'Authority and Leadership Questions', 'Both passages emphasize challenges to authority, with figures questioning who grants leadership. The phrase ''Who made thee a ruler'' parallels the inquiry about Jesus'' authority in the temple.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 24, 42, 6, 9, 9, NULL, 'Jesus'' Questioning Technique', 'This connection highlights Jesus'' method of engaging his audience through questions. Both passages feature Jesus asking a question to provoke thought and reflection on authority and moral action.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 24, 40, 10, 16, 16, NULL, 'Wisdom and Authority in Ministry', 'This connection highlights the theme of wisdom in the face of opposition. In both passages, Jesus emphasizes the need for discernment and strategy when engaging with challenging situations.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 24, 51, 4, 6, 6, 'by what authority I do these things', 'Authority and Grace in Speech', 'This connection highlights the importance of how one answers questions. In both passages, the emphasis is on the manner of response, whether it be through authority or with grace.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 24, 20, 26, 4, 5, NULL, 'Wisdom in Responding to Fools', 'This connection highlights the theme of how to engage with those who challenge authority or wisdom. Both passages emphasize the importance of discerning how to respond to folly, suggesting that careful consideration is needed in dialogue.', 'theme', 0.307, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 25, 62, 3, 20, 20, 'believe him', 'Heart and Belief Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief and internal conviction. In Matthew, the questioning of belief in John''s baptism reflects the struggle of the heart, which is further emphasized in 1 John, where the heart''s condemnation is addressed.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 25, 41, 1, 1, 11, 'the baptism of John, whence was it?', 'Connection of John the Baptist', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of John the Baptist''s ministry. Matthew''s inquiry about John''s baptism reflects the authority and divine origin of his role, which is elaborated in Mark as he prepares the way for Jesus through baptism and preaching.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 25, 40, 3, 1, 12, 'the baptism of John, whence was it?', 'Connection of John''s Baptism', 'This connection highlights the significance of John''s baptism as a divine calling. Both passages emphasize the authority of John''s message and the need for repentance, questioning the source of his baptism.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 25, 42, 20, 5, 5, 'If we shall say, From heaven;', 'Connection of Reasoning About John', 'Both passages emphasize the reasoning of the people regarding the source of John''s baptism. They present a similar dilemma about acknowledging its divine origin and the implications of disbelief.', 'parallel', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 25, 43, 1, 15, 15, 'believe him', 'Connection Between John and Jesus', 'This connection highlights the recognition of John the Baptist''s role in relation to Jesus. Both passages emphasize John''s testimony about Jesus, indicating his significance and divine authority.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 25, 43, 3, 18, 18, 'believe him', 'Belief and Condemnation Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief and its consequences. Both passages emphasize the importance of believing in divine authority, as seen in John''s baptism and in the name of the Son of God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 25, 40, 11, 7, 15, 'from heaven, or of men?', 'Connection Between John the Baptist', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of John the Baptist. In Matthew 21:25, the questioning of John''s authority reflects the broader recognition of his role as a prophet, which is affirmed in Matthew 11:7-15, where Jesus declares John to be more than a prophet.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 26, 41, 6, 20, 20, 'we fear the people', 'Fear of John the Baptist', 'Both passages emphasize the fear surrounding John the Baptist. In Matthew, the fear is expressed by the people regarding John''s prophetic status, while in Mark, Herod''s fear stems from recognizing John''s righteousness.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 26, 40, 11, 9, 9, 'John as a prophet', 'Connection Between John the Prophet', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of John as a prophet. In Matthew 21:26, the people''s view of John as a prophet influences the leaders'' response, while Matthew 11:9 affirms John''s prophetic role and suggests he is even more than that.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 26, 40, 14, 5, 5, 'we fear the people', 'Fear of the Multitude', 'Both passages emphasize the fear of the people regarding John as a prophet. In Matthew 21:26, the fear of the people influences the decision-making of the speakers, similar to how Herod''s fear of the multitude is noted in Matthew 14:5.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 26, 43, 5, 35, 35, 'John as a prophet', 'Connection Between John and Light', 'This connection highlights the recognition of John as a prophet in Matthew, which aligns with the description of John as a ''burning and a shining light'' in John. Both passages emphasize the significance of John''s role and the people''s response to his prophetic ministry.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 26, 23, 57, 11, 11, 'we fear the people', 'Fear of People and God', 'This connection highlights the theme of fear in both passages. Matthew discusses fearing the people regarding John as a prophet, while Isaiah questions whom one has feared, emphasizing a lack of remembrance of God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 26, 41, 11, 32, 32, 'for all hold John as a prophet', 'Connection of John as Prophet', 'Both passages emphasize the fear of the people regarding John, highlighting his recognized status as a prophet. This connection illustrates the shared concern of the speakers about public opinion on John''s prophetic role.', 'parallel', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 26, 42, 20, 6, 6, 'all hold John as a prophet', 'Connection on John as Prophet', 'Both passages emphasize the fear of the people regarding John's prophetic status. They highlight the dilemma faced by the speakers in acknowledging John's authority while fearing public backlash.', 'parallel', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 27, 45, 1, 18, 22, 'by what authority I do these things', 'Authority and Knowledge of God', 'This connection highlights the theme of authority and knowledge of God. In Matthew, the refusal to acknowledge Jesus'' authority parallels Romans'' depiction of those who do not glorify God despite knowing Him.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
